<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="lift-n">lift <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /lɪft/    美 /lɪft/  </p>
<p>[C]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.<strong>上升；举：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a lift in prices
涨价</p></div>

<h4 id="2-ame-elevator">2.★ <strong>电梯 (AmE elevator)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It's on the top floor. Let's <strong>take the lift</strong>.
在顶层呢，我们乘电梯吧。</p></div>

<h4 id="3-ride">3.★ <strong>搭便车 (ride)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Fortunately, we got a lift from a passing car. 
很幸运，有辆车经过，我们搭上了便车。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Do you think you could <strong>give me a lift</strong> to the station?
你能顺路载我去车站吗？</p><footer>2008 北京</footer></div>

<h4 id="4">4.<strong>振奋；鼓舞</strong></h4>
<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="give-sb-a-lift">give sb a lift</h3>
<p>1.<strong>让某人振奋起来：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The new park has given everyone in the neighbourhood a lift. 
新公园让附近的每个人都很开心。</p></div></div>